#Text=CyanogenMod : Open-source smartphone
#Text=OS goes commercial
#Text=Thursday , September 19 , 2013
#Text=File : CyanogenMod Cid . svg
#Text=CyanogenMod 's mascot , Cid .
#Text=Image : Cyanogen Inc. ( Image missing from commons : image ; log )

#Text=The developers of CyanogenMod , an open source free Android -based operating system for smartphones , announced yesterday their incorporation following a successful venture capital campaign which netted the open-source project a US$ 7 million nest egg , and plan to roll out a simple installation app on Google Play for their Android firmware .
#Text=Android runs nearly 80 % of new mobile devices ; CyanogenMod operates on at least 7 or 8 million of those .

#Text=CyanogenMod replaces the read-only-memory image in android devices which have been ' rooted ' — control acquired of the device 's superuser account — allowing continuing development for , and backporting abilities of new generations of the operating system to , older devices .
#Text=Investor Mitch Lasky wrote on his blog " We believe that CM is poised to become one of the largest mobile operating systems in the world .

#Text=The firm 's first announced step is to improve the process of installing the software on owner 's devices , which Kondik described as  hideous " .

column1: #Text=A new installer app is planned to be released " in the coming weeks " on Google Play .
#Text=The installer app will not require rooting the device , instead installing by simply clicking a button .
#Text=A further step , broadly described without any details , is a project with an unnamed original equipment manufacturer ( OEM ) .
#Text=" We have a least one OEM partnership in the works , there will be an announcement next week regarding our plans there " , said Kondik .
#Text=The team mentioned OEM licensing several times during the Q&A session on Reddit .

#Text=In addition to these corporate steps , there were questions regarding the roadmap for development of the ROM , which already has improvements regarding privacy and security over the native android loader .
#Text=With " plenty of things in the product pipeline already " Dutta lists additional security features , AirPlay mirroring , screen recording , and Voice+ as upcoming .
